# Resolution 2011-03-09.bg.1: LibreOffice as associated project

This resolution was adopted by the Board of Directors of SPI as a result
of a unanimous email vote on the spi-board mailing list.

### WHEREAS

1. LibreOffice is a substantial and significant Free Software project.

2. The LibreOffice developers would like SPI's support and assistance,
     including taking donations.

### THE SPI BOARD RESOLVES THAT

1. LibreOffice is formally invited to become an SPI Associated Project,
   according to the SPI Framework for Associated Projects, SPI Resolution
   1998-11-16.iwj.1-amended-2004-08-10.iwj.1, a copy of which can be found at
   [https://www.spi-inc.org/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1](/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1/)

2. The SPI liaison is selected by resolution of the LibreOffice steering
    committee, generally documented at
    [http://wiki.documentfoundation.org/TDF/Steering_Committee_Meetings](http://wiki.documentfoundation.org/TDF/Steering_Committee_Meetings)
    The initial liaison will be Sophie Gautier.

3. This invitation will lapse, if not accepted, 60 days after it is
   approved by the SPI Board.

